  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Aims of the study:

        -  to study the incidence rate of juvenile idiopathic arthritis (JIA) and it's clinical
           subtypes in Estonia for the years 1998-2000;

        -  to examine the course and short-term clinical outcome of JIA.

      Method: a prospective population-based study carried on in 14 counties of Estonia
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
